title: She's the One with the Funny Face
All the Hoffmeyers in the World
All the Trees in the Field
description: An old rancher tries to save his orange grove from real estate interests.

title: The Amateur
description: A young garment worker wants to be an actor.

title: From the Desk of Margaret Tydings
The House of the Seven Gables
Greybeards and Witches
description: A mother tries to protect her mentally ill son from the consequences of his behavior.

title: Pygmalion Jones
description: An accidental photograph catapults an obscure young woman from school teacher to pin-up girl and playgirl.

title: The Fall of the House of Usher
Horsepower
description: The patriarch of a Scandinavian immigrant family resists change, even down to keeping a gramophone for entertainment and horse team to plow his field. When he dies, his son becomes just as rigid and tries to continue on with the old ways.

title: On the Trail of the Klingsfeld
The Importance of Being Earnest
description: The formidable Lady Bracknell is quite willing that Algernon shall marry Cecily and her fortune. Jack, however, as Cecily's guardian, refuses his consent unless Lady Bracknell permits his marriage to Gwendolyn.

title: The Others
description: A governess battles to save two children from an evil supernatural force.

title: From the Desk of Margaret Tydings
description: Margaret, a pushy, quick-tempered lady executive, manages to make enemies at the office and a stranger out of her husband and son. When she keeps fainting and feeling ill, her doctor reveals she's being slowly poisoned.

title: A Hat, a Coat, a Glove
The Short Safari of B'wana Ben
Avenging of Anne Leete
description: An old man reminisces about his romance with a young woman named Anne Leete. One day many years ago, she did not appear for their usual rendezvous, and disappeared. Her broken-hearted sweetheart claims he saw her ghost six months later, and he resolves to secure a confession from the man he believes killed her.

title: The Man with the Pointed Toes
The Richest Man in the World
description: A young girl's boy friend is appalled at the way she plays on people's emotions for monetary rewards. She tries to make him understand that her meager salary will not support her aunt, her uncle and herself. When a rich old man comes to their small village, the girl goes immediately to strike up another friendship.

title: Daniel Webster and the Sea Serpent
Sing for Me
description: The story of a laundress who gains fame as a radio singer.

title: Out of the Frying Pan
description: Well known actors and actresses children played the roles of the stagestruck youngsters who drive a Broadway producer crazy trying to get parts in his new production.

title: The Collected Letters of Mr. Sage
Soldier's Boy
description: Gen. Stanton Brisk, on the day of his retirement from the Army, visits his wife Edith in a sanitarium. Ever since the day their son Edward was killed in the war, she has blocked off her mind to 24 years of married life and returned to the time when Edward was 12 and her husband was just a captain.

title: The Man Who Wanted to Hate
Eden End
description: With the return of young Wilfred Kirby from his job in British West Africa, the Kirby family is still not completely reunited. Stella, who left nine years ago for a career in the theater, still remains out of the family fold.

title: Goodbye on Thursday
description: A girl who lives on a boat with her father and brother feels that a newspaper editor's attentions toward her are a means of getting her father to stay in town and to continue his job as a linotype operator with the newspaper.

title: It Came from Out of Town
Much Ado About Nothing: Part 1
description: The Shakespeare classic, done live for this daytime color series, the first time a two part story was offered. It tells of a woman, a rich merchant's daughter about to be married to a man she loves, but a devious rival to the groom sets up an incident to fool him into thinking she's been sleeping around just before the wedding day.
